snippet.textDisplay: I'm glad he brought that up. so many guys think bench press is the pinnacle of testing strength. It has so much to do with physics and range of motion. A guy with short arms and a barrel chest will, of course, be able to press up more weight than a guy with long arms and a lean build. To each their own but I use a combination of resistance bands and free weights. I think bars, in the long run, cause more damage than benefit.

snippet.textDisplay: I train at home. Mostly works great but not having this kind of cable machine really leaves a gaping hole because nothing else can replace it. Can anyone recommend a cable machine like the one in the video that fits into a normal room and doesn't cost more than 1000 bucks?

snippet.textDisplay: 6 months I had a reverse shoulder replacement. The surgeon told me to never do a body weight pull up or a push up for.   the rest of my life. The concern is that the threading of the metal limb that was screwed into the scapula may prematurely wear loose. Besides joking around about being “screwed”, do you think the cable cross over with a reasonable rubber cable is a good way to keep the pecs looking fit?  Is it stressful on the glenoid to scapula connection.? Signed, appreciative senior age 73, Ray
